Preheat your oven to 220°C. Remove the puff pastry from your fridge. Halve, peel and
chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Roughly chop the
@chives{1}(roughly chopped - use scissors if easier). Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated - or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When
hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g}, onion and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}
to the #pan{} and cook until the lardons are golden and the veg has softened,
~{5-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons
> thoroughly.

Stir in half the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, chives, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @wholegrain
mustard{10%g} and @water for the sauce{150%ml} to the pan. Stir together, then
bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer the sauce until
slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}, then remove from the heat.

Once thickened, transfer the filling to an appropriately sized ovenproof #pie
dish{}. Cover with the @puff pastry sheet{1/2}, trimming off any excess. Press
some of the pastry over the side of the dish if you can, or just sit it on top.
Make a small hole in the middle - this allows the steam to escape.

> TIP: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}.

About 10 mins before the pie is cooked, trim the @green beans{150%g}. Clean out
the frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}.
Once the pan is hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char,
~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated - or use a garlic
press), turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add a splash
of @water{?splash} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some foil. Allow them
to cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Once the pie is baked, allow to stand for ~{2%minutes} before serving. When
everything is ready, divide the creamy bacon and mushroom pie between your
plates and serve with the garlicky green beans alongside. Enjoy!